I was one of the 1st to review this recipe, and have made it many times since, and offer the following. I've made it with and without the prosciutto. The difference is subtle, but worth it if you have prosciutto on hand. I follow the recipe (using less olive oil) until the point of putting the sauce and chicken together. I find that the chicken becomes too stewed and the sauce not thick enough. So, I continue to reduce and thicken the sauce on the cooktop, roast the chicken separately, then add both together for the last 10 minutes of baking. Hope this helps.

