Rating: 3
This was deliscious. Based on other review, I made a few modifications. I used 4 boneless breasts and 8 chicken legs. I also used Niman Ranch bacon instead of the prosciutto because I had it in the house. I cooked the bacon first, poured off most of the fat and then cooked the chicken breasts. I removed the breasts and browned the legs. I removed the legs and added a sliced onion, the garlic, rosemary, and sliced mushrooms, sauteed them for awhile and then added a whole can of crushed tomatoes and 1 cup broth. I added the legs back in and cooked in the oven for 30 min. When it was done, I put all the chicken in the fridge and cooked the sauce on low for 2 hours. I added 2 T tomato paste and an 8oz can of tomato sauce. I added the chicken back in and warmed it for 30 min and served over angel hair (I would use a thicker pasta next time.) Guests gave it rave reviews. The bacon gave it a subtle, smoky flavor.

