I rate this recipe 3 forks because there are, in fact, no provisions for thickening the sauce. Any cook with half a brain can deal easily with thickening a sauce using either arrowroot or a good old fashioned flour & cold water mixture. My family prefers more prosciutto & less chix bones, so I used 1.5 cups prosciutto & 4-5 boneless/skinless chix breasts. We were pleased with the results; very nice.

